    "creation_date" : 1295442649,
    "answer_id" : 4735607,
    "question_id" : 4110664,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Just encountered the same problem.  You can write a trivial custom deserializer for the <code>JsonElement</code> class:</p>\n\n<pre><code>import com.google.gson.Gson;\nimport com.google.gson.GsonBuilder;\nimport com.google.gson.JsonElement;\nimport com.google.gson.JsonObject;\n\nGsonBuilder gson_builder = new GsonBuilder();\ngson_builder.registerTypeAdapter(\n        JsonElement.class,\n        new JsonDeserializer&lt;JsonElement&gt;() {\n            @Override\n            public JsonElement deserialize(JsonElement arg0,\n                    Type arg1,\n                    JsonDeserializationContext arg2)\n                    throws JsonParseException {\n\n                return arg0;\n            }\n        } );\nString str = \"{ \\\"a\\\": \\\"A\\\", \\\"b\\\": true }\";\nGson gson = gson_builder.create();\nJsonElement element = gson.fromJson(str, JsonElement.class);\nJsonObject object = element.getAsJsonObject();\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
