    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The <code>JsonParser</code> constructor has been deprecated. Use the static method instead:</p>\n<pre><code>JsonObject asJsonObject = JsonParser.parseString(someString).getAsJsonObject();\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3460640,
      "reputation" : 4655,
      "user_id" : 2897869,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 52,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/JmkEF.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Hossein Kurd",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2897869/hossein-kurd"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1612423542,
    "creation_date" : 1612423542,
    "answer_id" : 66041043,
    "question_id" : 4110664,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><code>com.google.gson.JsonParser#parse(java.lang.String)</code> is now deprecated</p>\n<p>so use <code>com.google.gson.JsonParser#parseString</code>, it works pretty well</p>\n<p>Kotlin Example:</p>\n<pre><code>val mJsonObject = JsonParser.parseString(myStringJsonbject).asJsonObject\n</code></pre>\n<p>Java Example:</p>\n<pre><code>JsonObject mJsonObject = JsonParser.parseString(myStringJsonbject).getAsJsonObject();\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
